00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:52.680
Deception.

00:19:52.680 --> 00:19:55.950
One of my favorite magicians is Karl Germain.

00:19:55.950 --> 00:20:03.770
He had this wonderful trick where a rosebush
would bloom right in front of your eyes.

00:20:03.770 --> 00:20:09.070
But it was his production of a butterfly that
was the most beautiful.

00:20:09.070 --> 00:20:14.560
Ladies and gentlemen, the creation of lights.

00:20:14.560 --> 00:20:21.110
[children cheer]

00:20:21.110 --> 00:20:28.780
When asked about deception, he said this,
"Magic is the only honest profession.

00:20:28.780 --> 00:20:32.810
A magician promises to deceive you and he
does."

00:20:32.810 --> 00:20:36.500
I like to think of myself as an honest magician.

00:20:36.500 --> 00:20:43.410
I use a lot of tricks, which means that sometimes,
I have to lie to you.

00:20:43.410 --> 00:20:46.400
I feel bad about that.

00:20:46.400 --> 00:20:47.400
[laughter]

00:20:47.400 --> 00:20:49.070
But people lie every day.

00:20:49.070 --> 00:20:50.070
[phone rings]

00:20:50.070 --> 00:20:51.590
&gt;&gt;Woman: Hey, where are you?

00:20:51.590 --> 00:20:53.370
&gt;&gt;Marco: I'm stuck in traffic.

00:20:53.370 --> 00:20:55.820
I'll be there soon.

00:20:55.820 --> 00:20:58.280
We've all done it.

00:20:58.280 --> 00:21:01.380
&gt;&gt;Woman #2: I'll be ready in just a minute,
darling.

00:21:01.380 --> 00:21:04.490
&gt;&gt;Man #1: It's just what I've always wanted.

00:21:04.490 --> 00:21:07.110
&gt;&gt;Woman: You were great.

00:21:07.110 --> 00:21:08.110
[laughter]

00:21:08.110 --> 00:21:09.980
&gt;&gt;Marco: Deception.

00:21:09.980 --> 00:21:12.680
It's a fundamental part of life.

00:21:12.680 --> 00:21:20.520
Now, polls show that man tell twice as many
lies as a woman, assuming the woman he asked

00:21:20.520 --> 00:21:22.670
told the truth.

00:21:22.670 --> 00:21:25.410
We deceive to gain advantage.

00:21:25.410 --> 00:21:29.410
And to hide our weaknesses.

00:21:29.410 --> 00:21:35.580
The Chinese General Sun Tzu said that all
war was based on deception.

00:21:35.580 --> 00:21:40.140
Oscar Wilde said the same thing of romance.

00:21:40.140 --> 00:21:43.730
Some people deceive for money.

00:21:43.730 --> 00:21:46.940
Let's play a game.

00:21:46.940 --> 00:21:48.110
Three cards.

00:21:48.110 --> 00:21:49.950
Three chances.

00:21:49.950 --> 00:21:51.400
One five will get you ten.

00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:52.870
One ten will get you 20.

00:21:52.870 --> 00:21:54.270
Now, where's the lady?

00:21:54.270 --> 00:21:58.240
Where is the queen?

00:21:58.240 --> 00:21:59.490
This one?

00:21:59.490 --> 00:22:01.370
Sorry, you lose.

00:22:01.370 --> 00:22:02.370
[laughter]

00:22:02.370 --> 00:22:03.820
I didn't deceive you.

00:22:03.820 --> 00:22:06.970
You deceived yourself.

00:22:06.970 --> 00:22:08.460
Self-deception.

00:22:08.460 --> 00:22:13.391
That's why we convince ourselves that a lie
is a truth.

00:22:13.391 --> 00:22:18.860
Now, sometimes it's hard to tell the two apart.

00:22:18.860 --> 00:22:23.190
Compulsive gamblers are experts in self-deception.

00:22:23.190 --> 00:22:26.270
They believe they can win.

00:22:26.270 --> 00:22:29.180
They forget the times they lose.

00:22:29.180 --> 00:22:32.200
The brain is very good at forgetting.

00:22:32.200 --> 00:22:35.420
Bad experiences are quickly forgotten.

00:22:35.420 --> 00:22:42.440
Bad experiences quickly disappear, which is
why in this vast and lonely cosmos, we are

00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:46.850
so wonderfully optimistic.

00:22:46.850 --> 00:22:50.250
Our self-deception becomes a positive illusion.

00:22:50.250 --> 00:22:55.650
Why movies are able to take us on extraordinary
adventures.

00:22:55.650 --> 00:22:59.430
Why we believe Romeo, when he says he loves
Juliet.

00:22:59.430 --> 00:23:08.230
And why single notes of music, when played
together, become a sonata and conjure up meaning.

00:23:08.230 --> 00:23:09.930
That's Claire de Lune.

00:23:09.930 --> 00:23:17.500
It's composer Claude Debussy said that art
was the greatest deception of all.

00:23:17.500 --> 00:23:26.240
Art is a deception that creates real emotions--a
lie that creates the truth.

00:23:26.240 --> 00:23:41.400
And when you give yourself over to that deception,
it becomes magic.

00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:45.370
Thank you,

00:23:45.370 --> 00:23:49.350
[applause]

00:23:49.350 --> 00:23:52.520
We have already reached the end of my short
presentation.

00:23:52.520 --> 00:23:53.830
Thank you very much for coming.

